	<clause id="ch-tables-specification-matrix" obligation="normative"><title>TABLES AND SPECIFICATION MATRIX</title><clause id="_introduction_8" obligation="normative">
	<title>Introduction</title>
	<p id="_fe18e810-d7bd-409e-8414-da8715ae0802">As in previous editions, this edition of S-44 presents key elements of safety of navigation survey specifications in table format. This edition has two Tables (1 and 2) and provides a new specification <xref target="scl-matrix-description">Matrix</xref> for added flexibility for other types of hydrographic surveys carried out for purposes beyond safety of navigation. The new <xref target="scl-matrix-description">Matrix</xref> allows for customisation and enhancement of safety of navigation survey standards.</p>
	</clause>
	<clause id="_safety_of_navigation_standards" obligation="normative"><title>Safety of Navigation Standards</title><p id="_d4026043-d6f7-449a-8ffe-10743f3a31a7">Minimum bathymetry standards are defined in <xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/>. Other minimum standards for positioning and water flow measurements are defined in <xref target="tab-other-minimum"/>. Both tables must be read in conjunction with the detailed text in this document.</p>
(XML Line 000395): Hanging paragraph in clause
	<clause id="_safety_of_navigation_standards" obligation="normative"><title>Safety of Navigation Standards</title><p id="_d4026043-d6f7-449a-8ffe-10743f3a31a7">Minimum bathymetry standards are defined in <xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/>. Other minimum standards for positioning and water flow measurements are defined in <xref target="tab-other-minimum"/>. Both tables must be read in conjunction with the detailed text in this document.</p>
	<p id="_ca132a49-d7ba-43c0-ab8d-4363ce3a4f14">As stated above, all standards defined in <xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/> and <xref target="tab-other-minimum"/> are included in the specification <xref target="scl-matrix-description">Matrix</xref> within ranges of specification values which are available to enhance and customise safety of navigation surveys. Although the <xref target="scl-matrix-description">Matrix</xref> is available for this purpose, its usage will not reduce the minimum standards defined for safety of navigation survey orders. See Annex A for guidance on how to use the Specification <xref target="scl-matrix-description">Matrix</xref>.</p>
	<clause id="_bathymetry_standards" obligation="normative">
	<title>Bathymetry Standards</title>
	<p id="_56e57cad-f9ce-41b1-9e23-60d5274dd03b"><xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/> defines minimum bathymetry standards for safety of navigation surveys. The standards are intended to be purpose specific but technology independent in design. The order achieved for bathymetry data (<xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/>) may be assessed independently of order achieved for other positioning data (<xref target="tab-other-minimum"/>), so as not to unnecessarily degrade the representation of quality of bathymetry in nautical charts and products. <xref target="tab-minimum-bathymetry"/> follows.</p>
